- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the development and use of software (CRISTAL) for managing object lifecycle and provenance data. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries): The paper discusses the use of CRISTAL for data preservation in the High Energy Physics domain, which is related to digital libraries. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the use of CRISTAL in the construction and calibration of the CMS ECAL detector at CERN, which involves computational engineering and science. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper briefly mentions the N4U Analysis Service, which may involve programming languages for its implementation.
